translated: Kullenberg, Einar Börje, Ph.D., associate professor, Gothenburg, b. 11/5/06 in Uppåkra, Malmöhus. 1st son of Enoch K. and Anna Lindholm. Married in 1937 to Anna-Lisa Stendahl. Children: Gunnar b. 1938, Lars b. 1941, Anna Maria b. 1943. — Graduated from high school in 1924, B.A. in 1928, M.A. in 1934, Ph.D. in 1938. Assistant in the Swedish hydrobiological commission since 1931, associate professor in oceanography at Gothenburg University since 1942. Participated in numerous expeditions at sea from 1930-1947, study trip to Austria in 1939.

expeditions.description: Participated in numerous expeditions at sea.
